iii. Upward by half of the amount of budgetary grants, received and spent on capital outlays in excess of programmed levels (table above).   
iv. Downward for any shortfall in the targeted cash transfers (SEED) from their indicative target.   
v. Upward by the cost of severance payments associated with the restructuring of Grenada Concrete Emulsion and Production Corporation and the Grenada Postal Corporation (up to a cumulative maximum of $\cup\mathsf{S}\$4$ million);   
